1
00:00:05,302 --> 00:00:11,113
Look, even in this world
when you deal with romantic love,
 

2
00:00:11,113 --> 00:00:13,479
people will meet someone
and then they’ll say,
 

3
00:00:13,479 --> 00:00:16,223
“I have always 
and only loved you.”

4
00:00:16,423 --> 00:00:18,375
[Infinite Soul Mate]

5
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:22,003
They’ll say, “You mean … did you
say that to your ex-girlfriend?”

6
00:00:22,003 --> 00:00:25,003
[Laughing]

7
00:00:25,003 --> 00:00:28,868
They’ll say, “I have always
and only loved you.

8
00:00:28,868 --> 00:00:34,350
I only existed in anticipation
of meeting you.

9
00:00:34,350 --> 00:00:37,047
Now that I’ve met you
my life has meaning.

10
00:00:37,047 --> 00:00:41,094
I don’t know how I existed
before I met you.”

11
00:00:41,094 --> 00:00:43,548
I mean, I’m not actually
mocking these things;

12
00:00:43,548 --> 00:00:47,147
well, a little bit, but, no.
[Laughing]

13
00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:51,533
But, my point is we say that
and we mean it and we believe it,

14
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:57,524
and let’s not get into how often
it turns out to go otherwise.

15
00:00:57,524 --> 00:00:58,596
South Pole.

16
00:00:58,596 --> 00:01:04,569
But it’s a real thing,
that’s what we want,

17
00:01:04,569 --> 00:01:06,689
is that person that you meet

18
00:01:06,689 --> 00:01:11,272
who … 
coming in connection with them

19
00:01:11,272 --> 00:01:15,225
gives meaning and purpose
to your whole existence.

20
00:01:15,225 --> 00:01:17,812
Everything before that 
now suddenly becomes adjusted

21
00:01:17,812 --> 00:01:25,773
because you’ve met them, 
the love of your heart.

22
00:01:25,773 --> 00:01:28,937
And you think 
then you’re happy,

23
00:01:28,937 --> 00:01:31,470
that “Oh, now I know,
I have eyes, ears …”

24
00:01:31,470 --> 00:01:36,634
Everything is focused 
on the object of love, the beloved.

25
00:01:36,634 --> 00:01:40,026
If we can feel that way
—and we want to feel that way—

26
00:01:40,026 --> 00:01:42,938
if we can feel that way
about someone in this world,

27
00:01:42,938 --> 00:01:48,185
then magnify that 
to an infinite degree,

28
00:01:48,185 --> 00:01:49,586
and you can begin
to understand

29
00:01:49,586 --> 00:01:52,566
what we’re dealing with 
in Kṛṣṇa conception;

30
00:01:52,566 --> 00:01:57,004
the compelling, irresistible,
all-attractive beauty,

31
00:01:57,004 --> 00:02:00,711
seductive charm,
sweetness of Kṛṣṇa.

